9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 438, L.D. 670, “An Act to Address
10 Coercive Control in Domestic Abuse Cases”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 19-A MRSA §4102, sub-§1, ¶C, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 647, Pt. A, §3
14 and affected by Pt. B, §65, is amended to read:
15 C. Compelling a person by force, threat of force, coercion or intimidation:
16 (1) To engage in conduct from which the person has a right or privilege to abstain;
17 or
18 (2) To abstain from conduct in which the person has a right to engage;'
19 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
20 number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill. The
2233 amendment amends the definition of "abuse" for purposes of the protection from abuse
2244 laws to include compelling a person by coercion to engage in conduct from which the
2255 person has a right or privilege to abstain or to abstain from conduct in which the person has
2266 a right to engage.
